      "content": "Now that the mock data has been successfully created, we can proceed with the initial analysis script to determine the percentage of days in June from 2020 to 2023 where the maximum temperature in Houston, Texas exceeded 95\u00b0F.\n\n```python\n# filename: analyze_houston_weather.py\n\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Step 1: Load the data\ncsv_file = 'houston_weather_june_2020_2023.csv'\ndata = pd.read_csv(csv_file)\n\n# Step 2: Filter the data for the month of June\ndata['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])\njune_data = data[data['Date'].dt.month == 6]\n\n# Step 3: Determine the number of days where the max temperature exceeded 95\u00b0F\ndays_over_95 = june_data[june_data['MaxTemperatureF'] > 95].shape[0]\ntotal_days_june = june_data.shape[0]\n\n# Step 4: Calculate the percentage\npercentage_days_over_95 = (days_over_95 / total_days_june) * 100\n\nprint(f\"Percentage of days in June from 2020 to 2023 where the maximum temperature exceeded 95\u00b0F: {percentage_days_over_95:.2f}%\")\n```\n\nPlease run this script to get the desired percentage. Once executed, it will provide the likelihood in the format specified."
